<TITLE> 19 promoted to secretary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 4 (bdnews24.com)  The government has promoted 19 additional secretary-level officials to full secretary rank. Of the newly promoted officials, 18 were posted as acting secretaries in recent months to ministries and divisions including information, power, food, labour, social welfare, environment, planning and internal resources. The recommendations for promotion had already been made at a meeting of the Superior Selection Board, establishment secretary Iqbal Mahmud told bdnews24.com Tuesday. According to the establishment ministry order, the promoted officials are: Golam Mostakim, director general of Bangladesh Civil Service Administration Academy Nasiruddin Ahmed, acting secretary of internal resources division and chairman of National Board of Revenue Mohammad Habibullah Majumder acting secretary of planning division Mihir Kanti Majumder, acting secretary at environment and forests affairs ministry Samar Chandra Pal, acting secretary at rural development and co-operatives division Ilyas Ahmed, acting secretary at expatriates' welfare and overseas employments affairs ministry Mohammad Ataharul Islam, acting secretary at labour and employment ministry Mokhlesur Rahman, acting secretary at food and disaster management ministry Abdul Malek, acting secretary at IMED division Shafiul Alam, acting secretary at president's office AKM Abdul Awal Majumder, acting secretary at science, information and communications ministry Hedayet Ullah Al Mamun, acting secretary at civil aviation and tourism affairs ministry Kamrun Nesa Khanam, acting secretary at social welfare ministry Mahbubur Rahman, acting secretary at housing and public works ministry Mozammel Haq Khan, acting secretary at CHT affairs ministry Abul Kalam Azad, acting secretary at power division Manjur Hossain, acting secretary at local government division Kamal Abdul Naser Chowdhury, acting secretary at information ministry Mahbub Ahmed, acting secretary at youths and sports ministry bd
